## 2. Architecture Design
*Synthesized by Architecture Designer Agent*

### Core Technology Stack
- **Integration Layer**: MuleSoft Anypoint Studio (DataWeave 2.0 for transformations)
- **Endpoints**: Salesforce REST API, SAP BAPI/OData via MuleSoft SAP Connector
- **Security**: OAuth 2.0 over TLS 1.2/1.3 (HTTPS)
- **Deployment & Monitoring**: CloudHub 2.0 (iPaaS), Anypoint Monitoring & Alerts

### API-Led Connectivity Flow
```mermaid
graph TD
    SFDC[(Salesforce CRM)] <--> SAPI_SF[Salesforce System API]
    SAP[(SAP ERP)] <--> SAPI_SAP[SAP System API]
    
    SAPI_SF <--> PAPI[Customer Sync Process API]
    SAPI_SAP <--> PAPI
    
    PAPI --> Alert[Email Alerting Service]
    PAPI --> Log[(Anypoint Monitoring)]
```
**Architecture Overview:** We will utilize a standard API-led 3-tier architecture. System APIs will abstract the physical connectivity to Salesforce and SAP. The Process API will orchestrate the near real-time polling, execute the DataWeave transformation, perform data validation, and trigger email alerts upon failure.

